cannot be translated Deacon, but a Servant;
because this word Deacon, is appropriate through vse, Math. 2. 20. to Church-seruants.

Illucescere here, is taken for the rising of the starres; 
   Answ. 
 therefore they are called Stellalucis, Psal. 148. 3.

Thirdly, he blessed the first Cup of Wine, and sayd; 
                           1. Cup.
                           Blessed art thou, O Lord God, King of the world, who hast made the fruit of the vines.

                    The vniust Iudge feareth neither God nor Man: the 
                    Luke 18. Affirmatiue, The Iust Iudge feares both God and Man;

but it will not follow affirmatiuely and negatiuely, The iust Iudge feares God, but not man.

We come to the knowledge of God three manner of Illust. wayes. 1. Alsted. Metaph.
                  Per viam negationis, Godis not this nor this; Ergo, He is this: we proceed here, as the Caruer of an Image doth, when he heweth off from the stone, this and this, to make it this. 2. Per viam causatonis, as when we take him vp by his effects. 3. Per viam eminentiae;
                  Rom. 1. what excellent thing we see in the creatures, that leads vs to take vp what excellency is in God.
